Class##A blueprint for creating objects. It defines the data and behavior an object can have.
Object##An instance of a class. Objects are created from class blueprints.
Method##A block of code that performs a specific task and can be called when needed.
Field##A variable that belongs to a class or object and stores data.
Variable##A named storage location in memory that holds a value.
Constructor##A special method used to create and initialize a new object.
Parameter##A variable listed in a method header that receives a value when the method is called.
Argument##The actual value passed into a method when it is called.
Return Type##The type of value a method sends back after it finishes running.
void##A return type that means a method does not return any value.
main Method##The starting point of a Java program where execution begins.
String##A sequence of characters used to store text.
int##A primitive data type used to store whole numbers.
double##A primitive data type used to store decimal numbers.
boolean##A primitive data type that stores either true or false.
char##A primitive data type that stores a single character.
if Statement##A control structure that runs code only when a condition is true.
else Statement##A control structure that runs alternate code when an if condition is false.
for Loop##A loop that repeats code a set number of times using initialization, condition, and update parts.
while Loop##A loop that repeats code as long as its condition remains true.
Array##A fixed-size structure that stores multiple values of the same type.
ArrayList##A resizable list object that can store multiple values and grow or shrink as needed.
Index##The position of an element in a list or array, starting at 0.
Encapsulation##The practice of bundling data and methods together in a class and controlling access to them.
Inheritance##A feature where one class can extend another class and reuse its fields and methods.
Subclass##A class that inherits from another class.
Superclass##The parent class that another class extends from.
Override##To provide a new version of an inherited method in a subclass.
this##A reference to the current object being used inside a class.
static##A keyword that makes a field or method belong to the class itself rather than an object instance.
final##A keyword used to make a variable unchangeable, a method not overridable, or a class not extendable.
Access Modifier##A keyword like public or private that controls where a class member can be accessed from.
public##An access modifier that allows a class, field, or method to be used from anywhere.
private##An access modifier that allows a field or method to be used only inside its own class.
Getter##A method that returns the value of a private field.
Setter##A method that changes the value of a private field.
Scanner##A Java class commonly used to read user input or file input.
Exception##An event that disrupts normal program flow, often caused by an error.
try##A block used to wrap code that might throw an exception.
catch##A block used to handle an exception thrown by code in a try block.
Null##A special value meaning a reference points to no object.
toString##A method that returns a String representation of an object.
Import##A statement that allows a Java file to use classes from other packages.
Package##A namespace used to organize related Java classes.
Compile##To translate Java source code into bytecode that the JVM can run.
JVM##The Java Virtual Machine, which runs compiled Java bytecode on different systems.
Comment##Text in code meant for humans and ignored by the compiler.
End Of Deck##This is the end of the deck.